FAQs
What are the basic requirements to study medicine in Poland?
The basic requirements include a high school diploma with strong grades in science subjects, language proficiency (usually in English), and passing entrance exams specific to the university or country.

Is studying medicine in Poland expensive?
While tuition fees and living expenses vary, studying medicine in Poland is often more affordable than in countries like the USA or UK. Scholarships and financial aid can also help reduce costs.

How can I apply for scholarships to study medicine in Poland?
You can apply for scholarships through the universities you’re interested in, as well as through government programs and private organizations. Qadri-International can assist you in finding and applying for suitable scholarships.

Are Polish medical degrees recognized worldwide?
Yes, Polish medical degrees are widely recognized and respected globally. Graduates often have the qualifications needed to practice medicine in various countries around the world.

What support can Qadri-International provide for prospective medical students?
Qadri-International offers comprehensive support, including university selection, application assistance, visa processing, and pre-departure guidance, ensuring a smooth and successful journey to studying medicine abroad.
